article.description: Esho leads UMass past La Salle 71-65 in A-10 play
article.headline: Esho leads UMass past La Salle 71-65 in A-10 play
article.linkText: Esho leads UMass past La Salle 71-65 in A-10 play
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Maxie Esho scored 19 points and grabbed a career-high 12 rebounds to lead UMass past La Salle 71-65 on Wednesday night. It was the redshirt senior's second career double-double and first this season. Derrick Gordon added 13 points for UMass (8-7, 1-1 Atlantic 10), which made 27 of 52 (52 percent) field goals. A pair of free throws by Jordan Price pulled La Salle (8-7, 0-2) within one, 61-60, with five minutes to play, but the Explorers went 2 of 9 from the field down the stretch. Layups by Esho and Gordon gave UMass a five-point lead before Steve Zack made the second of two free throws to make it 65-61. Esho and Trey Davis each made both ends of one-and-one opportunities in the final 1:45 to hold off La Salle. Cleon Roberts scored 17 and Zack had 16 points and four blocked shots for the Explorers. Jerrell Wright grabbed 13 rebounds.
